similarity.py — Semantic similarity scoring

Computes Similarity(A, B) using explicit field overlap.

Formula:
Similarity(A, B) =
w_invariant * invariant_overlap +
w_neighbor  * neighbor_overlap  +
w_domain    * domain_overlap    +
w_failure   * failure_mode_overlap +
w_transfer  * transfer_overlap

Default weights (tunable per query context in v0.2):
invariant_overlap:    0.35
neighbor_overlap:     0.20
domain_overlap:       0.10
failure_mode_overlap: 0.15
transfer_overlap:     0.20
“””

